            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>SEOUL, Jan 22 (Reuters) - South Korea's special prosecution team said on Thursday it has  filed an appeal after a court sentenced former President Yoon Suk Yeol on charges including obstructing attempts to arrest him following his failed bid to impose martial law. </p><p>\n              The Seoul Central District Court last week sentenced the ex-president to five years in prison in the case. Yoon could have faced up to 10 years in jail over the obstruction charges.</p><!-- Article --><p></p><p> (Reporting by Heejin KimEditing by Ed Davies)</p></div>",
