            "title": "Uvalde police officer acquitted of child endangerment in deadly Texas school shooting",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>Jan 21 (Reuters) - A Texas jury on Wednesday found a former police officer not guilty of felony child-endangerment charges for his role in the law enforcement response to the 2022 Uvalde school shooting that killed 19 elementary students and two teachers.</p><p>\n              Adrian Gonzales, 52, who belonged to the Uvalde school district police force, had faced 29 counts of child endangerment for what prosecutors said was his failure to stop a gunman in the first minutes of one of the deadliest school shootings in U.S. history. The gunman was later shot dead by other officers.</p><!-- Article --><p></p><p> (Reporting by Andrew Hay in Taos, New Mexico; Editing by Steve Gorman and Christian Schmollinger)</p></div>",
